BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:Montclair State University
CATEGORIES:Arts
CATEGORIES:Academic/Educational
CATEGORIES:Cultural
CATEGORIES:Medium Size
CATEGORIES:Casual/ Relaxed
DESCRIPTION:The Department of Art & Design presents the Spring 2026 Art Fo
 rum series. Art Forum is a speaker series featuring artists\, designers\,
  art historians\, curators\, and art critics from around the world presen
 ting their work and ideas in an open forum.  \n \nThe next speaker in thi
 s engaging series is painter\, Ginny Casey who is known for her surreal\,
  dreamlike compositions. She will discuss her work and share insights int
 o her latest projects.\n \nGinny Casey paintings feature decrepit interio
 rs teeming with objects such as chisels\, woodcutters\, pulleys\, and boo
 ks that are distorted\, engorged\, disproportioned\, and rendered biomorp
 hic. Casey’s environments estrange the domestic\, casting shades of anxie
 ty\, perversity\, and discomfort on everyday items. Architecture in her w
 ork follows a dream logic\, with trap doors\, staircases leading to nowhe
 re\, and ladders extending into the abyss.\n \nCasey’s process begins wit
 h drawings of individual objects\, which she redraws and collages togethe
 r to build relationships and narratives. She works intuitively\, allowing
  stories to emerge from her subconscious without preconceived notions of 
 the finished painting. Her practice draws upon psychoanalysis\, free asso
 ciation\, dreams\, and the unconscious\, encouraging open interpretation 
 and engaging viewers in a world “like trying to see in the dark.”\n \nCas
 ey received her MFA from the Rhode Island School of Design. She has had s
 olo exhibitions at Half Gallery\, New York\; Nino Mier Gallery\, Los Ange
 les\; and the Institute for Contemporary Art\, Philadelphia. Her work has
  also appeared in group exhibitions at The Hole\, NY\; Almine Rech\, New 
 York\; Blum & Poe\, Los Angeles\; Gagosian Gallery\, New York\; Paul Kasm
 in Gallery\, New York\; and Nino Mier Gallery\, Brussels.\n \n📅 Art Foru
 m\nMonday\, 4/13/26  5:20pm-7pm\nCalcia Hall\, Room 140\nFree and open to
  the public \n\nHosted by: Art and Design\n\nAdditional Information can b
 e found at: https://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12415277
DTEND:20260413T230000Z
DTSTAMP:20260412T030706Z
DTSTART:20260413T212000Z
GEO:40.859750;-74.199750
LOCATION:Calcia 140\, Calcia Hall
SEQUENCE:0
STATUS:CONFIRMED
SUMMARY:Art Forum featuring Ginny Casey
