DESCRIPTION:\nThis panel will feature four accomplished women professional
 s in Public Health who will share their personal and professional journey
 s. They will reflect on their experiences navigating leadership\, advocac
 y\, and service as women in the field. Their stories will inspire meaning
 ful dialogue about resilience\, empowerment\, and equity in Public Health
 .\nFollowing the panel discussion\, students will engage in a hands-on se
 rvice initiative\, assembling hygiene kits for a local non profit organiz
 ation. Our goal is to assemble 100 hygiene kits for our community members
 .\nBy pairing storytelling with direct community engagement this event ai
 ms to educate and mobilize students to become informed about the issues c
 ommunity members face. \n \n\n \n\nHosted by: Daughta Speaks\, Latin Amer
 ican Student Organization\n\nAdditional Information can be found at: http
 s://montclair.campuslabs.com/engage/event/12412569
