DESCRIPTION:The CSAM Science Teaching Program holds biweekly meetings that
  are open\, welcoming\, and inclusive! Any student curious about science 
 teaching is invited to join us. Each meeting highlights a theme related t
 o science education\, from classroom strategies to career pathways\, and 
 offers students opportunities to connect with mentors\, explore internshi
 ps\, and gain real-world experience working with teachers and children. S
 tudents are encouraged to bring a guest who may also be interested in exp
 loring science teaching.\nThese gatherings help us build a strong communi
 ty of support\, where students encourage one another\, share experiences\
 , and access valuable opportunities such as scholarships\, paid internshi
 ps\, and mentoring from advanced peers and in-service science teachers. W
 hether you are just beginning to explore the idea of teaching or already 
 on the path toward certification\, these meetings are a place to grow\, l
 earn\, and belong.\n\nHosted by: College of Science and Mathematics (CSAM
 )\n\nAdditional Information can be found at: https://montclair.campuslabs
 .com/engage/event/11712551
